title: Did Johns Hopkins Student Newspaper Retract Article Claiming COVID-19 Deaths ‘Not Above Normal’?
subtitle: The story reportedly questioned the accuracy and credibility of reported U.S. COVID-19 deaths.
author: Madison Dapcevich
vclaim: An article titled “COVID-19 Deaths: A Look at U.S. Data” was published in the Johns Hopkins student-run newspaper on Nov. 22, 2020, and subsequently retracted.
